                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13165882" author="charith" created="Fri, 9 Dec 2011 06:22:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As a Fix for this  i have introduced new nhttp properties to be defined at nhttp.properties file &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;http.socket.timeout.receiver = Socket timeout for Listner&lt;br/&gt;
http.socket.timeout.sender = Socket timeout for Sender. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669586" author="charith" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 19:08:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fix is in the trunk. Hence resolving the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13743065" author="hiranya" created="Sun, 18 Aug 2013 00:04:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is probably broken now, with the recent changes done in the NHTTP transport. Also this has to be implemented for PT transport as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13743091" author="hiranya" created="Sun, 18 Aug 2013 01:08:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed for both NHTTP and PT transports. Two new properties are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;http.socket.timeout.listener&lt;br/&gt;
http.socket.timeout.sender&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Documentation updated. Added test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
